article.headline: Portland State 64, Montana State 56
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. (AP) -- Jason Erickson scored 16 of his 21 points in the second half Saturday to help Montana State rally to a 64-56 victory over Portland State. Portland State (9-13, 3-6 Big Sky) took a 49-39 lead on a 3-pointer by Seth Scott with 8:40 remaining before Montana State (12-10, 4-5) went on a 17-2 run and took a 56-51 lead on a put-back by Nick Dissly with 3:37 remaining. Portland State pulled to within 56-53 on free throws by Will Funn and Blake Walker. Erickson made a layup with 1:59 remaining and PSU's Seamus Boxley hit two free throws with 1:31 left to cut the lead to 58-55 before the Bobcats hit 6-of-8 free throws in the final 90 seconds. Boxley led PSU with 22 points and nine rebounds, followed by Walker with 13 points and eight rebounds. Frank Brown added 14 points for the Bobcats, who held an 11-6 lead after two free throws by Matt Towsley with 15:22 left in the half. The Vikings used a 19-3 run to take a 25-14 lead on a free throw by Boxley with 6:11 left in the half. MSU went nearly nine minutes in the first half without a field goal and trailed 29-22 at halftime.
